==English==

===Noun===
'''[[peak]] [[oil]]'''

# The peak of the [[Earth]]'s oil [[production]].  The rate of extraction of oil from a region of any size, from a single well, to a nation, continent or the world, follows a bell curve over time.  Before the peak of the curve of extraction, the oil is under high pressure, generally of better quality, and generally easier to bring to market.  After the peak, oil tends to be of lower quality, under lower pressure and more technically difficult to extract.  After the peak in a given region, rate of extraction declines inexorably.